features: SOME BY MI : SOME BY MI is a compound word of ‘SOMETHING’ and ‘BY A MIRACLE’. Our brand mission is to make products that stick to the essentials of cosmetics, with safe and clean ingredients with proven efficacy. Through our Skincare products, we hope to bring some positive changes and ‘MIRACLES’ to your skin

MIRACLE TONER : This facial toner contains high-content (10,000 ppm) tea tree water extract which improves trouble skin quickly and mildly. The exfoliating toner includes AHA/BHA/PHA & Papaya extract & Witch Hazel extract to remove dead skin and body wastes. It passed dermatological testing for sensitive skin and includes patented ingredients P-PEFINYL (sebum controlling component) and FRUCTAN (moisturizing)

KEY INGREDIENTS : AHA exfoliates the surface of the skin and can help to reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles and improve the skin texture and tone. BHA exfoliates the inside of the pores, help to clear out impurities and excess sebum. PHA is a gentle exfoliator which help to hydrate the skin, brighten the skin, reduce the appearance of fine lines, and improve the overall texture of the skin

MIRACLE LINE : MIRACLE Lines are suitable for acne-prone skin, containing high amounts of Tea Tree Leaf to improve the skin. This line has optimally mixed AHA, BHA, PHA to refine dead skin cells and impurities, and Truecica, an exclusive calming agent, that maintains healthy-looking skin and prevents acne-breakout through pH balance care. Free of 20 harmful ingredients and passed irritation test for sensitive skin

SOME BY US : We make products with proven efficacy only by undergoing strict testing from the planning & developing stages to product launch, in collaboration with various dermatology experts. If you have any questions about our products, please do not hesitate to contact us. Your satisfaction is the ‘First Priority Goal’ of SOME BY MI

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this product
reviews.reviewText: I love this toner. The first time I bought it from YesStyle. I actually was about to buy it from there again but decided to check if Amazon has it and it did! I ordered it right away. Prices are the same but delivery is almost 2 weeks faster than YesStyle. Not overly drying for my skin even in Wisconsin's winter. After cleansing amd washing my face, I put this on a cotton pad and wipe my entire face with it. I can still see the leftover dirt or whatnot on the cotton pad. Decreases my breakouts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not the best for my skin type
reviews.reviewText: I have sensitive-dry skin and have been looking for a good toner to help with redness/evenness. I currently have acne and have had it for a couple months now. When I first used this it did burn quite a bit but once I continued to use it my skin got used to it. It has helped a bit but overall not much has changed. I definitely think that if you have sensitive skin like me you may want to try something else such as Anua’s 77% or MEDIPEEL Phyto Cica-Nol (this one works best for me)But I wouldn’t say this is a bad product. Definitely try it out if you are looking for a decent toner and if it doesn’t work look for another one. What I have realized is that people’s skin are all different, even with the same skin type people’s skin will respond differently to certain products. You just have to try things out until you find what is right for you!
